FURgKkRFtMK5yKbjYZVVwA
Windsor is brought to you by Upward Projects, the team of superhero masterminds behind the much loved Postino Winecafes. They sneak into our dreams at night and create restaurants inspired by our innermost wishes and dreamscapes of the perfect urban bistro.  At least that's what I thought when I walked into Windsor. "Damn, they nailed it again. I love this place. They have got to be infiltrating my head."  Comfortable but cool interior, great patio, large bar area for some neighborhood camaraderie and a little food voyeurism, and a zigzagged wall that says "YES!" in big red letters. Know what I say to that? You guessed it! It's YES, btw.  The bartender deserves a gold star for being totally attentive, soooo friendly, and a bonus glittery star for being too darn cute. Actually, all of the service staff were really, really nice. Gold stars for everyone!  The mixed grain salad was just one more reason I will be returning ASAP. I added smoked salmon and, holy moly! It was like 4th of July in my mouth with all the flavor explosions. I agree with some other reviews that a  couple of bites were a little overwhelmed by orange zest, but still loved the dish overall. Seafood ceviche was scrumptious, but not quite revelatory.  The guy next to me ordered a pork sandwich that looked out of this world. It also looked big enough to have it's own gravitational pull, and on second thought it probably did, because the entire bar area pivoted to stare, mouths agog. He said  "shish ish sho schmood", and that's a good enough endorsement for me. I'm coming back. And I want that sandwich.  Nice wine and beer list, and some very refreshing sounding cocktails with all manner of blueberry this and lemonade that.  Wake me up. I must be dreaming.

